HEADWORD: Sack-winged
<hw>Sack"-winged`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having a peculiar pouch developed near the front edge of the wing;
-- said of certain bats of the genus <gen>Saccopteryx</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
